A survey in Shanghai and Beijing revealed that people in the 7-12 and 60-70 age groups are at higher risk of obesity, with males more affected than females.
Improved lifestyles and poor eating habits contribute to the problem.
In Guangzhou, teenagers face anemia and obesity due to malnutrition and unhealthy eating habits.
Kuwait is also battling high obesity rates, especially among women, leading to chronic ailments.
The UAE is facing a diabetes epidemic, with rising rates linked to obesity.
These health issues highlight the importance of education and preventive measures to combat the growing problem.
